---
import DocumentationLayout from '../layouts/DocumentationLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../components/sections/Callout.astro';
import TryInClaudeCode from '../components/sections/TryInClaudeCode.astro';
import { buildWebPageJsonLD } from '../utils/seo';
import installTruth from '../data/install_truth.json';
import heroGetStarted from '../assets/heroes/hero_get_started.png';

// Every command on this page renders from the install-truth fixture (single source;
// gate-12-install-truth asserts the page matches it and the fixture matches the
// template checkout). Never hardcode an install command here. (ADR-034: canonical
// face = aDNA-Network/aDNA, a clone-and-run workspace image; 1-command flow.)
const { commands, workspace_root, canonical_repo_https, legacy_repo_https } = installTruth;

const jsonLD = buildWebPageJsonLD({
  title: 'Get Started with aDNA',
  description:
    'Set up your own local aDNA workspace in one command: clone the workspace image from GitHub — router pre-instantiated, standard embedded — and let your first agent session scaffold your first project.',
  url: Astro.url.href,
});
---

<DocumentationLayout
  title="Get Started"
  description="Set up your own local aDNA workspace in one command: clone the workspace image from GitHub — router pre-instantiated, standard embedded — and let your first agent session scaffold your first project."
  jsonLD={jsonLD}
  heroImage={{
    src: heroGetStarted,
    alt: 'Cozy pixel-art scene of a desk and computer with a glowing cyan DNA helix rising from the screen — a new aDNA workspace coming alive',
  }}
>
  <p>
    Set up your own aDNA workspace — a local, agent-readable home for every project's context — in
    about 5 minutes. Everything lives on your machine; nothing is sent anywhere.
  </p>

  <Callout variant="info" title="Prerequisites">
    <p>
      Git, and <a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Claude Code</a>
      installed via <code>npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code>. Obsidian is optional — vaults are
      plain Markdown, so any editor works.
    </p>
  </Callout>

  <Callout variant="tip" title="What you'll have when you're done">
    <p>
      A <code>{workspace_root}/</code> workspace that ships ready: the workspace <code>CLAUDE.md</code> router
      (your agent's map between projects) pre-instantiated at the root; the standard itself embedded in a hidden
      <code>.adna/</code> folder (your agent reads it, never edits it — updates arrive with <code>git pull</code>
      at the workspace root); and your first <code>&lt;name&gt;.aDNA/</code> project, scaffolded for you by the
      onboarding interview, with its own git history — kept out of the workspace image's history by design.
    </p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="step-1">1. Clone the workspace</h2>
  <p>
    The clone <em>is</em> your workspace — not a template you copy from. The router comes pre-instantiated
    and the standard comes embedded; there is nothing to bootstrap by hand.
  </p>
  <pre class="cmd"><code>{commands.clone}</code></pre>

  <h2 id="step-2">2. Start Claude Code</h2>
  <p>
    Run <code>{commands.launch}</code> in the workspace. The agent reads the router, sees a fresh workspace
    with no projects yet, and walks you through creating your first one:
  </p>
  <pre class="cmd"><code>{commands.enter}
{commands.launch}</code></pre>
  <pre><code>$ {commands.launch}
✓  Loaded CLAUDE.md (workspace router)

This is a fresh aDNA workspace — the standard is in place and
there are no projects yet. Let's create your first one.

What is this project called, and what problem does it solve?
&gt; _</code></pre>
  <p>
    The interview scaffolds <code>&lt;your_project&gt;.aDNA/</code> — its triad of
    <code>what/</code>&thinsp;·&thinsp;<code>how/</code>&thinsp;·&thinsp;<code>who/</code>, its governance
    files, and its own git history. When it finishes, your workspace looks like this:
  </p>
  <pre><code>{workspace_root}/
├── CLAUDE.md            # workspace router (ships with the clone)
├── .adna/               # the standard (embedded; read-only — releases update it)
└── my_project.aDNA/     # your first project — a working context graph
    ├── CLAUDE.md        # the project's own governance
    ├── what/            # knowledge: context, decisions, artifacts
    ├── how/             # operations: sessions, missions, skills
    └── who/             # people: roles, coordination</code></pre>
  <p>
    From here, work happens <em>inside</em> projects: <code>cd my_project.aDNA &amp;&amp; {commands.launch}</code>
    and the agent picks up that project's governance automatically.
  </p>

  <Callout variant="info" title="The whole flow, one command">
    <p>
      Both steps, chained — auditable inline, nothing executed from the network:
    </p>
    <p class="cmd-oneliner"><code>{installTruth.one_liner}</code></p>
  </Callout>

  <Callout variant="info" title="Existing installs (pre-June-2026 layout)">
    <p>
      Installed earlier, with a cloned hidden <code>.adna/</code> plus a copied router? It keeps working:
      the previous template repository is preserved read-only at
      <a href={legacy_repo_https} target="_blank" rel="noopener">adna-legacy</a>, and your clone's old URLs
      redirect there — frozen, so nothing underneath you changes. To move to the current layout, run the
      standard's <code>skill_workspace_upgrade</code> from your workspace.
    </p>
  </Callout>

  <TryInClaudeCode />

  <h2 id="next-steps">Next steps</h2>
  {/* Storyweave P3 / M3.2 — the north-star bridge: make the loop explicit (you built a node → it
      joins a living network), not just a list of "learn more" links. */}
  <p>You just built a node in a living network. Grow it — then see where it connects:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Where it joins:</strong> the <a href="/vaults/">living registry</a> of vaults and <a href="/network/">the network</a> your project can federate with — building in the open is the whole point.</li>
    <li><a href="/learn/what-is-adna">What is aDNA?</a> — the five-minute conceptual tour</li>
    <li><a href="/learn/concepts/triad">The Triad</a> — why every project splits into what / how / who</li>
    <li><a href="/learn/tutorials/first-claude-md">Tutorial: Create Your First CLAUDE.md</a></li>
    <li><a href="/learn/tutorials/navigate-a-vault">Tutorial: Navigate a Vault</a> — reading a context graph like an agent does</li>
    <li><a href="/learn/concepts/knowledge-graph">Knowledge graphs</a> — what your workspace grows into</li>
    <li>See it live: the <a href={canonical_repo_https} target="_blank" rel="noopener">aDNA repository</a> is the workspace image itself — clone it and you are holding everything this page described.</li>
  </ul>
</DocumentationLayout>

<style>
  /* H-8: copy-critical install commands must be fully readable at 320–390px — soft-wrap them
     (the long clone URL + the one-liner) rather than hide them behind horizontal scroll. Scoped
     to the command blocks only; the illustrative ASCII tree + interview output keep the default
     overflow-x:auto so their alignment is preserved. */
  pre.cmd {
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
  }
  .cmd-oneliner code {
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    word-break: break-word;
  }
</style>
